{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1783475665,"nonce":"stQAUpBgkPxdRx3PLwLcuYucIVo=","title":"Retire the PostgreSQL `canonical.rs` string normalizer by structurally lowering the two remaining check/generated/index expression shapes it still absorbs.","message":"After PR #90 (general `ExprNode::Function` node), a column-argument user/built-in function check lowers structurally, so `canonical.rs` no longer normalizes those. But `crates/squealy-postgresql/src/canonical.rs` (~1175 lines: a hand-rolled PG boolean-expression tokenizer + Pratt parser + serializer) is still load-bearing for the residual `ExprNode::Raw` shapes the structural grammar cannot yet invert. Local codex on #90 confirmed deleting it would regress those (e.g. an authored `amount % 2 = 0` check churns against pg's `((amount % 2) = 0)` deparse). `canonical_check_expression` (crates/squealy-postgresql/src/lib.rs) keeps its `Raw` string-normalizer fallback for them.\n\n\n1. **`%` modulo** — there is no `ArithmeticOp::Modulo` variant, so `lower_expr` bails to `NotYetLowered` → `Raw`.\n2. **A general `CAST`** — inverting the cast target name is dialect-specific and, for MySQL, ambiguous (its cast vocabulary `SIGNED`/`UNSIGNED`/`DOUBLE`/`CHAR`/`DECIMAL` does not map one-to-one back to a neutral `SqlType` width). Only pg's *synthesized redundant literal* casts are stripped today; a genuine user cast stays `Raw`.\n\n(A quoted function name and a direct-literal-argument general function also stay `Raw` by design — those are lossy to structure and are out of scope; they belong in a `raw` expression.)\n\n\n- **`ArithmeticOp::Modulo`** end-to-end: new IR variant + arithmetic symbol `%` (symmetric across PG/MySQL/SQLite, no dialect divergence) in `render_scalar_expr` + the query renderers; `lower_binary` maps `BinaryOperator::Modulo` → `Modulo`; macro emitter / KDL ser-de; normalize/walkers. Then an authored `%` check re-plans to empty structurally.\n- **General cross-dialect `CAST` inversion**: teach `lower_expr` to invert a general `CAST(x AS ty)` per dialect into `ExprNode::Cast`, resolving the MySQL `SIGNED`/`UNSIGNED`/width ambiguity (or refusing to fold where semantics can't be preserved, falling back to `Raw`). This is the deferred \"carry-forward (b)\" from the Phase-1 plan.\n- Once both land (and any other residual `Raw`-check shape is confirmed structurable), **delete `canonical.rs`** and simplify `canonical_check_expression` to match the other three seams (re-parse `Raw`, keep verbatim if still un-structurable). Port `canonical.rs`'s unit tests (the regression spec: literal-cast stripping, `IN`↔`ANY/ARRAY`, `BETWEEN`, `LIKE`↔`~~`, boolean flattening, identifier quoting, `%` arithmetic) into the structural round-trip corpus first.\n\n\nA squealy-published table carrying a `%`-modulo or general-`CAST` check re-plans to empty **structurally** (no string normalizer), and `crates/squealy-postgresql/src/canonical.rs` is deleted.\n\nRelates to epic acb1c6d (Phase 1) and 108fdfc.","files":null}]}